## What Not To Do

- Do not compete first as another agent runtime.
- Do not compete first as another observability dashboard.
- Do not pitch every industry before one wedge has adoption proof.
- Do not bury `UNVERIFIABLE`; make it the proof of honesty.
- Do not let browser control become the whole story. Browser evidence matters
  because it joins to receipts and verdicts.
- Do not make the creative engine the first enterprise GTM motion unless the
  demos are polished and measurable.
- Do not overclaim a unique moat. The current evidence supports strong
  differentiation, but not a proven monopoly on the combined pattern.

